  "baseRefName": "main",
  "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds the **Revenue Execution & Scale Control layer (V7)** for Dealix, converting the company OS into a **daily, review-only operating machine** for founder actions, revenue execution, diagnostic delivery, proposal generation, proof assets, CEO briefs, board reports, market intelligence, knowledge base, operating memory, automation boundaries, scale readiness, crisis response, and a master command center.\n\nThe core rule is enforced everywhere: **AI prepares. Founder approves. Manual action only. No external sending.**\n\n## Includes\n\n**OS doc layers** (`docs/`)\n- Revenue Execution OS · Delivery Conversion OS · Proof Asset OS\n- Market Intelligence OS · Knowledge Base OS · Operating Memory OS\n- Automation Boundaries OS · Scale Readiness OS · Crisis / Kill-Switch OS\n- Master Startup Command Center\n- Final Control Tower & Company Utilization evidence reports\n\n**Generators** (`scripts/`, all review-only, send-blocked)\n- `commercial_generate_400_drafts.py` (400 review-only drafts)\n- `founder_action_queue_generate.py`\n- `founder_revenue_dashboard.py`\n- `diagnostic_pack_generate.py`\n- `proposal_seed_generate.py`\n- `proof_asset_template_generate.py`\n- `daily_ceo_brief_generate.py`\n- `weekly_board_report_generate.py`\n- `market_intelligence_brief_generate.py`\n\n**Validators / verify gates**\n- `revenue_manual_events_validate.py` · `operating_memory_validate.py`\n- `revenue_execution_verify.py` · `master_startup_command_verify.py`\n- `startup_os_verify.py` · `final_launch_control_verify.py` · `company_utilization_verify.py`\n\n**Tests** — 28 tests across 15 files\n**GitHub Actions** — `revenue-execution-verify.yml`, `master-startup-command-center.yml` (workflow_dispatch + schedule, `permissions: contents: read`, artifact-only, no secrets, no sending, no commits)\n**Config / data** — `config/market_intelligence_signals.json`, `config/operating_memory_schemas.json`, `data/revenue_manual_events.example.jsonl`\n\n## Safety\n- No external sending. No SMTP. No WhatsApp outbound. No LinkedIn automation.\n- No website auto-submit. No scraping. No secrets.\n- A defense-in-depth scanner in `revenue_execution_verify.py` fails the build if any generator/validator contains an external-send pattern.\n- All external action remains manual and founder-approved.\n\n## Tests Run (real results)\n\nVerify gates — all PASS (exit 0):\n```\n[revenue_execution_verify] PASS\n[master_startup_command_verify] PASS (10 OS layers)\n[startup_os_verify] PASS (10/10 layers)\n[final_launch_control_verify] PASS\n[company_utilization_verify] PASS\n```\n\nV7 pytest suite:\n```\n28 passed in 0.88s\n```\n\n`make env-check` → PASS. `ruff check` on all V7 files → clean.\n\n**Not run in this environment** (require the full app stack — pydantic/httpx — not installed in the isolated sandbox; unrelated to V7):\n- `make api-contract-check`, `make prod-verify`, full `make test` (app import deps)\n- `make security-smoke` surfaces only **pre-existing** fake-secret fixtures in unrelated `tests/` and `docs/` files; **no V7 file is flagged**.\n\n## Final Go / No-Go\n\n**GO**\n- Daily founder command center · 400+ review-only drafts · founder action queue\n- Manual outreach planning · diagnostic pack generation · proposal draft generation\n- Revenue dashboard · CEO daily brief · weekly board report\n- Proof asset preparation · scale readiness tracking\n\n**NO-GO**\n- Automated sending · WhatsApp cold outreach · LinkedIn automation · bulk email\n- Paid ads live launch · fake traction · external sending from Actions\n\nGenerated runtime artifacts are written under `outputs/` (git-ignored; CI uploads them as artifacts).\n\n---\n_Generated by [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code/session_01JxvwQmCXpKr98mBAdCcW5d)_",
